    "question": "Problem 2.10. Consider the reaction $\\mathbf{A}\\rightarrow \\mathbf{B} + \\mathbf{C}$ (with particle masses $\\mathfrak{m}_{\\\\mathbf{A}}, \\mathfrak{m}_{\\\\mathbf{B}}, \\mathfrak{m}_{\\\\mathbf{C}}$ )。\\n(c) If A decays while moving in the lab frame, find the relation between the angle at which B comes off, and the energies of A and B.",
