    "solution": "(c) In this case $\\mathbf{P}_{\\\\mathbf{A}} = (\\\\mathbf{E}_{\\\\mathbf{A}},\\\\mathbf{\\\\underline{P}}_{\\\\mathbf{A}}),\\\\mathbf{P}_{\\\\mathbf{B}} = (\\\\mathbf{E}_{\\\\mathbf{B}},\\\\mathbf{\\\\underline{P}}_{\\\\mathbf{B}}),$ so (1) becomes\\n$$- \\\\mathsf {m}_{\\\\mathbf {A}}^{2} - \\\\mathsf {m}_{\\\\mathbf {B}}^{2} + 2 \\\\mathsf {E}_{\\\\mathbf {A}} \\\\mathsf {E}_{\\\\mathbf {B}} - 2 (\\\\mathsf {E}_{\\\\mathbf {A}}^{2} - \\\\mathsf {m}_{\\\\mathbf {A}}^{2})^{\\\\frac {1}{2}} (\\\\mathsf {E}_{\\\\mathbf {B}}^{2} - \\\\mathsf {m}_{\\\\mathbf {B}}^{2})^{\\\\frac {1}{2}} \\\\cos \\\\theta = - \\\\mathsf {m}_{\\\\mathbf {C}}^{2}.$$"
